# Angular 22 workspace rules

Read `AGENTS.md` first. It is the canonical source for project facts,
commands, testing constraints, and completion criteria.

- Keep TypeScript strict. Prefer inference and `unknown`; avoid `any`.
- Use standalone declarations without explicit `standalone: true`.
- Use `input()`, `model()`, `output()`, signals, `computed()`, and `inject()`.
- Set `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush` on components.
- Use decorator `host` bindings instead of `@HostBinding`/`@HostListener`.
- Use native `@if`/`@for`/`@switch` template control flow.
- Use native class/style bindings instead of `NgClass` and `NgStyle`.
- Keep templates accessible and preserve labels, keyboard behavior, focus,
  errors, and disabled state.
- Follow ESLint, Prettier, and EditorConfig without unrelated formatting churn.

`NgxMaterialIntlTelInputComponent` is not a `ControlValueAccessor`. Use
`fieldControlName` inside a parent `[formGroup]` or bind an existing control
through `[fieldControl]`. Never put `formControlName` or `[formControl]`
directly on this component unless it is intentionally converted into a real
value accessor.
